Parliament, Sunday, 11 March 2018 – The Portfolio Committee on Home Affairs urges all potential voters above the age of 16 years to visit voting stations today to register for the 2019 National and Provincial elections. The Committee further urge those already on the voters roll to visit stations to check their details or register in the correct voting districts. "Anyone with service delivery issues should use his/her vote to express their views. Our forebears fought for us to be able to vote for our government. Let us register to exercise this democratic right, said Mr Lemias Mashile, the Chairperson of the Committee. ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON HOME AFFAIRS, MR LEMIAS MASHILE. Media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Malatswa Molepo (Mr)
